															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lilyflower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1876818); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1876818&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204187" alt="LilyFlower" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1876818)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lilyflower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1876818); return false;" >LilyFlower</a></span> <span class="odate time_1525351184 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 May 2018 12:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3789032">
									

<p>So when I first wrote this, I didn't expect to actually publish it. Or to show anyone, even. But I decided to, and an hour later, it was posted.</p>
<p>I'm not going to comment on the content, or the implications, or whatever. I'm a big proponent of &quot;there is no canon&quot; so that's for you to decide. I have my own headcanon for this, and you could probably work it out. I've given you the clues.</p>
<p>A lot of people have commented on the length, or the apparent lack of content. I've always found, for me, trying to fit as much depth into as little prose as possible is how I prefer to write. Kinda why I like reading poetry. It's alright if you don't think there's enough here, or whatever. There's enough for me.</p>
<p>I think this is the most important thing, to me, that I've written. I'm glad I can share it.</p>

							</div>

